(1, 'Home', 'html', '', '<h1>Dada HelpDesk</h1>\n<p>Dada HelpDesk is a simple IT HelpDesk application. It can be used within a company to manage the IT help requests. <br /> <br /> The users belong to three different groups:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Managers</li>\n<li>Employees</li>\n<li>IT staff</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Here is the typical workflow:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Employees</strong> can send an <strong>IT help request</strong>, specifying the details, a picture and a due date</li>\n<li>The <strong>manager</strong> receives an email (enable it from the config file include/config_prepackaged_app.php) when a new request is registered and assigns the request to a member of the IT staff</li>\n<li>Each member of the <strong>IT staff</strong> can see the requests and add comments, asking for details to the employee who created the request</li>\n<li>The <strong>employees</strong> can also add comments to the requests they created</li>\n<li>When the work is done and after a final supervision, the manager can change the <strong>status</strong> of the request to "Solved"</li>\n<li>For some of the requests, the manager needs to print and sign a <strong>request form paper</strong>; to print the paper the manager can open a request in details mode, choose the help_request template and click on "Produce PDF".</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The manager has a <strong>dashboard</strong> page that clearly displays the following info:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The last requests submitted</li>\n<li>The more urgent requests submitted and still unsolved</li>\n<li>A pie chart representing the request by status (Solved, Assigned, Unassigned)</li>\n<li>A bar chart representing the workload of the staff members</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The whole application has been developed WITHOUT writing any PHP or Javascript CODE.</strong></p>\n<p>You can <strong>login</strong> as a manager (user: manager), employee (user: bob, alice, silvia or penny) or IT staff (user: rob, barry or ian). <br /> <br /> You can also login as "root": root can do everything including add/modify users and groups and edit the DaDaBIK application itself.<br /> <br /> All the users have, as password, the installation password you chose.</p>', 1, 'top', 1, '', 'n', 'y'),
(2, 'Manager''s Dashboard', 'PHP', 'dashboard', '<p>Draft content</p>', 2, 'top', 1, '', 'n', 'n');
